04 Apr 2019 02:55






I'll be honest: maybe I'm jaded, but the  premise I found kinda lukewarm, going in.

The excellence here comes by virtue of how it ties into the existing  involving Pattern Screamers. It's a wonderfully vicious, no-holds-barred apocalyptic companion piece to the subtle creep of 3930. It doesn't need to stand on it's own because it exists to up the stakes. And it does so brilliantly.

I love this flavor of existential horror that so deftly casts nonexistence as something less of a concept and more of a character, and never going too hammy about it.







